revision.text:
'''Cape Torson''' ({{coord|66|40|S|90|36|E||display=inline,title}}) is a point at the east side of [[Posadowsky Bay]] on the coast of [[Antarctica]]. First mapped from air photos taken by [[U.S. Navy Operation Highjump]], 1946-47. Remapped by the Soviet expedition 1956, who named it after Lieutenant [[K.P. Torson]], of the ship Vostok in the Bellingshausen expedition 1819-21.

{{usgs-gazetteer}}

