[[File:Elisabeth Lichtenberger 1984 Intern.Geographenkongress Wien Exkursion.jpg|thumb|Lichtenberger in 1984]]
'''Elisabeth Lichtenberger''' (17 February 1925 – 14 February 2017) was an Austrian geographer. Her research focus was on [[urban geography]] and [[mountain research]], particularly in [[Central and Eastern Europe]] and [[North America]]. She taught at the [[University of Vienna]], and was awarded the [[Austrian Decoration for Science and Art]] in 1999.<ref name="award">{{cite news|title=Österreichisches Ehrenzeichen für Wissenschaft und Kunst Kurie für Wissenschaft|url=https://wissenschaft.bmwfw.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/Ehrenzeichen_Inlandsmitglieder.pdf|accessdate=4 March 2017|agency=Government of the Republic of Austria|language=de}}</ref> She was a fellow of the [[British Academy]], a member of [[Academia Europaea]] and the [[Austrian Academy of Sciences]],<ref name="OEAW">{{cite news|language=de|title=Trauer um Elisabeth Lichtenberger|url=http://www.oeaw.ac.at/en/austrian-academy-of-sciences/the-oeaw/article/trauer-um-elisabeth-lichtenberger/|accessdate=4 March 2017|publisher=Austrian Academy of Sciences}}</ref> and holder of honorary doctorates from the [[University of Chicago]] and [[Leipzig University]].
Born in Vienna on 17 February 1925, she died on 14 February 2017, aged 91.<ref name="award"/><ref name="OEAW"/>
