'''Jarun Bridge''' ({{lang-hr|Jarunski most}}) is a planned [[bridge]] that will cross the [[Sava|Sava River]] in [[Zagreb]], the capital of [[Croatia]]. The bridge will be located in the western part of the city, [[Trešnjevka - jug|Trešnjevka]] near Lake [[Jarun]]. 

The city of Zagreb organized a tender for the design of the Jarun Bridge in 2006,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vjesnik.hr/html/2008/02/19/Clanak.asp?r=zag&c=2 |title=Uz idealne okolnosti, gradnja Jarunskog mosta tehnički moguća već ovoga ljeta |newspaper=[[Vjesnik]] |date=2008-02-19 |accessdate=2011-01-18 }}{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and accepted the project in 2007.<ref name="VL">{{cite web|url=http://www.vecernji.hr/zg-vijesti/most-za-bicikliste-i-pjesake-spojit-ce-laniste-i-jarun-632181|title=Most za bicikliste i pješake spojit će Lanište i Jarun|work=[[Večernji list]]|date=24 October 2013|language=hr|accessdate=26 March 2015}}</ref> The construction, originally estimated to cost around €40 million, did not start due to a lack of funds. {{As of|2013}} the city is considering a pedestrian-and-cycle design as a cheaper alternative.<ref name="VL"/>

